festival.introText:
Thank you for making Highest Point 2022 the best yet - see you all 11th - 14th May 2023

Every year after the dust settles (or in the case of this year we washed our wellies) we always leave Williamson Park with a big smile, proud of the show we put on for the people of Lancaster and beyond. Moments later, we start pulling apart the events of the weekend, trawling through feedback, our own notes, video footage, photos and memories of what had gone before us, to start work on 2023 and make sure we improve what we can and build on what we already loved – in May you will have seen an improved woods stage, better signage, no more payment wristbands, a bigger fence, a different control room, more bars and a completely different main stage.

Some of this you might have noticed and it made a huge difference to you, other bits made a huge difference to the running of the festival and you had no idea we had even done it. You see – we will never ever become complacent about Highest Point and stop developing it – it’s a project that will never be finished. We have many, many things that we want to address from 2022 but we feel the biggest is the audience. We absolutely want Highest Point Festival to be a family-friendly event where ALL are welcome so any changes we make to 2023 will have that as our main goal.

For May 2023 we plan to:

  • Increase the free age for children to 12 years old
  • Teens (13 – 17 years) need to be accompanied by a parent or guardian aged 30+ (up from 21+)
  • Children & Teens should have one adult per two minors
  • Our medical and welfare will be located in a larger, quieter area
  • A new welfare team will work across the site to reunite any unattended minors
  • Better wristbands. Crimping them was a rubbish idea!

                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Highest Point is to be enjoyed by everyone, and we know there are things that need addressing so everyone feels welcome and comfortable. Hopefully this goes someway to helping with that.

X

Highest Point

faqs.question: Does Highest Point have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Highest Point is a non-camping festival so camping equipment is not needed. However, there is plenty of alternative accommodation to choose from in Lancaster.

faqs.question: How can I apply for a Personal Assistant/Disabled Parking Ticket?
faqs.answer:
Please purchase the tickets you require for Highest Point Festival via Skiddle, not including the Personal Assistant ticket.

We then ask you to supply us with one of the following documents dated within the past 12 months or with valid date covering the event:

-The front page of the DLA letter with the PIP letter

-The front page of Attendance Allowance letter

-Evidence of being registered as severely sight impaired (blind)

-Recognised Assistance Dog ID card

-Valid Access Card showing you require a +1 to accompany you

 

For a disabled parking space we will need an image of your Blue Badge. Please be aware there is a limited number of disabled spaces available and these will be allocated on a first come first service basis.

 

If you could email the supporting document and your Skiddle order ID number to info@highestpoint.co.uk we can add a Personal Assistant ticket to your order.

faqs.question: When is Highest Point 2023?
faqs.answer: Highest Point returns to Williamson Park from Thursday 11th to Sunday 14th May 2023.

faqs.question: How much are Highest Point tickets?
faqs.answer:
Adult tickets for 3 days at the festival start at just £145 + booking fee.

Adult tickets for 2 days at the festival start at just £135 + booking fee.

Adult day tickets for Friday or Saturday start at just £69.50 + booking fee, with Thursday Adult day tickets starting from just £39.50 + booking fee.

 

13-17 Kids tickets for 3 days at the festival start at just £80 + booking fee.

13-17 Kids tickets for 2 days at the festival start at just £70 + booking fee.

13-17 Kids day tickets for Friday or Saturday start at just £35 + booking fee, with Thursday 13-17 Kids day tickets starting from just £20 + booking fee.

 

0-12 Kids tickets are free.

faqs.question: How do I get to Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
By Car - You can reach Williamson Park via Junction 34 of the M6. There will be designated parking close to the festival site at North West Auctions. As the festival is in a residential area, road closures will be in place.

By Rail - Lancaster is the closest rail station and is approximately a 10 minute taxi ride or 30 minute walk. 

By Taxi - Yes, there is a taxi rank at Lancaster station. We  encourage you to share  taxis with fellow festival goers where possible.

By Foot - The festival is a 10 minute walk from Dalton Square.

faqs.question: I have requested disabled parking, where is the car park?
faqs.answer:
The disabled car park is situated on the University of Cumbria campus. Please use the postcode LA1 3JD. This car park is opposite the site entrance. 

Please turn either left or right off Bowerham Rd into the University campus, you will be met by a steward who will request your name & provide you with a disabled car park pass. 

 

How to get from car park to Highest Point Entrance: 

From the car park, please follow a path where you will pass a football pitch on your right then the University of Cumbria Sports complex on your left. Next, cross Wyresdale Rd which is closed for the duration of the festival. Finally, you will reach Highest Point Festival main entrance where you will have your ticket(s) scanned and you will receive your wristbands.

faqs.question: Where is Highest Point?
faqs.answer: Highest Point is located in Williamson Park, Lancaster. It takes about 5 minutes to get there from the town centre by bus, or car. The entrance to Highest Point Festival is located on Wyresdale Road. The postcode is LA1 3EA.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available for Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
Yes, payment plans are available for Highest Point Festival:

Three Day Adult Ticket: £15* deposit plus 4x payments of £35*

Two Day Adult Ticket: £15* deposit plus 4x payments of £32.50*

Friday OR Saturday Adult Ticket: £5* deposit plus 4x payments of £18.75*

 

* + booking fee

faqs.question: Where can I park at Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
North West Auctions

Exit the M6 at junction 34 and head towards Lancaster city centre. Please follow Highest Point diversion signs directing you to the event car park.

Disabled access Car Park - How to find the car park:

University of Cumbria, Lancaster Campus

Access via Bowerham Rd, Lancaster, LA1 3JD

 

Please follow your sat nav as the Highest Point diversion signs will route you to an alternate car park.

faqs.question: Where are the disabled toilets?
faqs.answer: These will be located all across the park. You will be able to locate them on the map in the Highest Point Festival guide which will be provided at the festival entrance. Furthermore, Highest Point has an app that contains a full festival map with key facilities highlighted.

faqs.question: Does Highest Point have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
Highest Point is a family festival and therefore there aren't any age restrictions. Children are able to attend the full duration of the festival and do not have to leave the event at a certain time in the evening.

 

Please note, anyone aged 17 years old and under will need to be accompanied by an adult aged 21+ at all times throughout the event. You may be asked to show a photo ID upon entry.

faqs.question: How do I access my tickets?
faqs.answer: Your RapidScan tickets will be available via your Skiddle account or confirmation email. Head to www.skiddle.com/orders or the 'my tickets' section within the app, for quick easy access.

faqs.question: Can I access the disabled viewing platform?
faqs.answer: If you require access to the viewing platform, please email through to info@highestpoint.co.uk with your requirement.  Please note, there is limited availability on the viewing platform so a space is not guaranteed.

faqs.question: Can I leave and re-enter Highest Point?
faqs.answer: Yes, but you must be back before the advertised last entry time. Please note, you may be subject to another search upon re-entering the festival.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does my child need to have a ticket for Highest Point?
faqs.answer: All Highest Point festival goers must have a ticket for entry, no matter the age.

faqs.question: What are the stage times at Highest Point?
faqs.answer: Stage times will be published on our social media channels nearer to the event and will be displayed at the festival.

faqs.question: Can I pass on my tickets privately?
faqs.answer:
Yes, you can pass them on to family, friends or work colleagues so that they can use the tickets at the event instead. Please see the article below on how you can change the name on the order.

 

https://bit.ly/3eQen75

faqs.question: Can I park at Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
Yes, parking is available. How to find the car park:

North West Auction

Exit the M6 at junction 34 and head towards Lancaster city centre. Please follow Highest Point diversion signs directing you to the event car park.

Disabled Car Park - How to find the car park:

University of Cumbria, Lancaster Campus

Access via Bowerham Rd, Lancaster, LA1 3JD

 

Please follow your sat nav as the Highest Point diversion signs will route you to an alternate car park.

faqs.question: I have a multiple-day ticket but now cannot attend one of the days, can I give a day ticket to someone else?
faqs.answer: No, when you arrive at the festival you will be given a wristband permitting entry for the rest of the event. As a result, we cannot split multiple-day tickets.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Highest Point. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options. 

 

If you have special dietary requirements please email info@highestpoint.co.uk and we can help accommodate this.

faqs.question: Can I bring my dog to Highest Point?
faqs.answer: No dogs are allowed on site for the festival, with the exception of guide dogs / assistance dogs.

faqs.question: Can I bring my camping chairs?
faqs.answer: Due to security restrictions you are unable to bring camping chairs into the festival. You are welcome to bring a picnic blanket along with you as there is plenty of space available.

faqs.question: What are the ground conditions like at Highest Point?
faqs.answer:
Highest Point takes place at Williamson Park in Lancaster, home to the iconic Ashton Memorial and is set in 54 acres of parkland with woodland walks & play areas.

 

The event will be held within the parkland and you’ll find that some areas within the site will be uneven. There are plenty of tarmac pathways within the park, with the stages easily accessible.

 

Please prepare for all scenarios; consider the ground conditions and the unpredictable English weather!
